A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing October 9, 2025, as PANDAS Awareness Day at the state capitol; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, pediatric acute-onset neuropsychiatric syndrome (PANS) and pediatric
4 autoimmune neuropsychiatric disorder associated with streptococcal infection (PANDAS)
5 create the sudden onset of obsessive-compulsive disorder in children, causing previously
6 healthy and emotionally well-adjusted children to experience severe anxiety and emotional
7 disturbances; and
8 WHEREAS, children with PANS and PANDAS experience some or all of the following
9 symptoms: tics or other abnormal movements, severe separation anxiety, generalized anxiety,
10 irritability, aggression, personality changes, attention deficit hyperactivity disorder, marked
11 deterioration in learning and school performance, and developmental regression, including
12 regression in handwriting; and
13 WHEREAS, children with PANS and PANDAS may experience a moderate to dramatic
14 improvement with antibiotics, intravenous immunoglobulin (IVIG) treatment, or
15 plasmapheresis; and
